cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SY

The paper proposes a meta-learning approach to building effective and generalizable MCMC proposals using neural networks. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method is applied to several applications including open-universe Gaussian mixture models (cs.CV), and a real-world named entity recognition task (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of neural networks for fast approximations to block Gibbs conditionals may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
